The '''Albania national youth football team''' are the national under-20, under-19, under-17 and now also under-15 [[Football (soccer)|football]] teams of [[Albania]] and are controlled by the [[Football Association of Albania]]. 

The under-20 squad is often cited as a [[Farm team|feeder squad]] to the [[Albania national under-21 football team|under-21 squad]]. Most of the player picked for this team are U-21 internationals already. [[Albania]] have never played a game with the U-20 squad and the team was only formed after an invitation to play in [[2009 Mediterranean Games]] in [[Pescara]], [[Italy]].

The under-19 squad participates in mostly regional tournaments, the most important being the [[UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship]].

The under-17 squad participates in two important tournaments. The [[UEFA European Under-17 Football Championship]] and the [[FIFA U-17 World Cup]]. [[Albania]] has never qualified to a U-17 finals.

The under-15 squad participates in regional tournaments. It was formed on June 25, 2009 by the [[Football Association of Albania]]. The federation appointed former [[Albanians|Albanian]] international, [[Sulejman Demollari]] as the team's first ever manager.<ref>[http://www.albania-sport.com/mat.php?idm=11235 Albania U-15 formed]</ref>

